/\/www.ultrasaurus.com\/sarahblog\/archives\/000227.html\">What&#8217;s that bug?<\/a><br \/>\n* <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ultrasaurus.com\/sarahblog\/archives\/000129.html\">work as play<\/a><br \/>\n* <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ultrasaurus.com\/sarahblog\/archives\/000265.html\">stage fright<\/a><br \/>\n* <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ultrasaurus.com\/sarahblog\/archives\/000187.html\">MLK&#8217;s American Dream<\/a><br \/>\n* <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ultrasaurus.com\/sarahblog\/archives\/000158.html\">art walking on the beach<\/a><\/p>\n<p>Maybe in a year or two, I&#8217;ll have some more categories&#8230; or perhaps even more hard to categorize posts.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.ultrasaurus.com\/sarahblog\/archives\/000063.html\">read more<\/a> top ten reasons for a web log<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Almost four years ago, I started writing a series about why I keep a weblog. One key reason on my list is that this weblog has helped me find my voice. When I started blogging, I thought my blog would be full of technical tips and practical insights from my love of coding. As it&hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ultrasaurus.com\/2007\/08\/finding-my-voice\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a> <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ultrasaurus.com\/2007\/08\/finding-my-voice\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":84,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[1],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.ultrasaurus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/307"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.ultrasaurus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.ultrasaurus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.ultrasaurus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/84"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.ultrasaurus.com\/